<h4 id="1-why">1. Why</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Why study linear algebra, because it’s simple, and can solve practical problems.</li>
  <li>Why gaussain distribution, it’s simple.</li>
  <li>Not because it’s related to the central limit therom.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="2-example">2. Example</h4>

<h4 id="21-conditional-distribution">2.1 Conditional Distribution</h4>

<p>The conditional distribution of $X_1$ given known values for $X_2=x_2$ is a multivariate normal with:</p>

\[\begin{array}{l}
\mu_{1}+\Sigma_{12} \Sigma_{22}^{-1}\left(\mathrm{x}_{2}-\mu_{2}\right) \\ 
\Sigma_{11}-\Sigma_{12} \Sigma_{22}^{-1} \Sigma_{21}
\end{array}\]

